We have to do this tonight.

503
00:47:20,380 --> 00:47:21,400
Where?

504
00:47:21,430 --> 00:47:23,510
It's a safe house in El Poblado.

505
00:47:24,470 --> 00:47:25,470
We've used it before.

506
00:47:26,560 --> 00:47:28,180
Berna knows where.

507
00:47:28,850 --> 00:47:30,390
[Judy]
I'll see you there.

508
00:47:48,750 --> 00:47:51,210
Everything is ready, Judy. Get in.

509
00:47:52,670 --> 00:47:54,040
Let's go, Flaco.

510
00:48:01,930 --> 00:48:03,470
[in English]
She's on her way.

511
00:48:09,390 --> 00:48:11,850
[in Spanish]
I know what you're thinking.

512
00:48:14,690 --> 00:48:17,940
I'm making a mistake. [chuckles]

513
00:48:19,190 --> 00:48:23,170
You'll be taken care of
like you've taken care of me.

514
00:48:23,200 --> 00:48:26,720
The only thing that needs to happen
is to get rid of the Cali cartel.

515
00:48:26,740 --> 00:48:27,910
Up here, Flaco.

516
00:48:42,170 --> 00:48:44,680
I can't protect a rat.

517
00:48:49,810 --> 00:48:52,020
[static, stops]

518
00:49:02,190 --> 00:49:05,320
I didn't think you'd betray me.

519
00:49:06,530 --> 00:49:08,910
You were going to get yourself killed,
Judy.

520
00:49:10,040 --> 00:49:12,640
So now, you're going to get on that plane.

521
00:49:12,660 --> 00:49:15,640
And if I don't, what? What happens?

522
00:49:15,670 --> 00:49:18,690
If you don't get on,
then you'll leave with the Castaños.

523
00:49:18,710 --> 00:49:20,750
And I won't protect you anymore.

524
00:49:52,120 --> 00:49:53,540
Tell me something.

525
00:49:54,870 --> 00:49:56,870
Did Cali arrange this?

526
00:49:59,330 --> 00:50:01,940
How much did they offer you?
At least tell me that.

527
00:50:01,960 --> 00:50:06,010
It's a mutual understanding.
I'll work with the Castaños.

528
00:50:07,300 --> 00:50:11,570
They don't understand our business,
but they'll be useful in mine.

529
00:50:11,600 --> 00:50:15,350
- So you fucked over your partner.
- I was never your partner.

530
00:50:16,060 --> 00:50:18,150
I only protected your life.

531
00:50:19,600 --> 00:50:24,250
Relax. You'll have money.

532
00:50:24,280 --> 00:50:27,530
The Americans said they'd make sure
you had everything you need.

533
00:50:28,410 --> 00:50:31,280
- Where am I going?
- Doesn't matter.

534
00:50:32,660 --> 00:50:36,830
Go. And never come back to Colombia.

535
00:50:43,420 --> 00:50:45,130
Don't worry about a thing.

536
00:50:45,840 --> 00:50:51,510
You'll still be a rat, but for the CIA,
instead of the DEA.

537
00:51:14,490 --> 00:51:16,370
[in English]
Hey, man. How's it going?

538
00:51:17,540 --> 00:51:19,370
Everything good at the safe house?

539
00:51:21,170 --> 00:51:23,250
- Where's Messina?
- Oh, she's gone.

540
00:51:24,880 --> 00:51:27,150
Reassigned. Headed home.

541
00:51:27,170 --> 00:51:31,240
Likely to spend the rest of her career
busting meth labs in Indianapolis.

542
00:51:31,260 --> 00:51:33,570
Something about chain of command.

543
00:51:33,600 --> 00:51:36,180
- And Judy?
- You didn't hear?

544
00:51:36,930 --> 00:51:42,210
Judy has an interview
with the Miami Herald in, uh...

545
00:51:42,230 --> 00:51:44,210
oh, about five hours.

546
00:51:44,230 --> 00:51:48,250
Now I can't be certain,
but I bet she has a story to tell

547
00:51:48,280 --> 00:51:52,490
about the involvement of a certain
DEA agent with Los Pepes.

548
00:51:55,280 --> 00:51:57,850
All I know for sure is,
whatever Judy has to say,

549
00:51:57,870 --> 00:51:59,960
it won't be pointed in my direction.

550
00:52:01,410 --> 00:52:03,210
You should've stayed in your lane.

551
00:52:04,460 --> 00:52:05,500
[whispers] Wow.

552
00:52:06,750 --> 00:52:08,670
And Cali too, right?

553
00:52:10,420 --> 00:52:11,880
They get a pass?

554
00:52:16,050 --> 00:52:18,160
How much do they pay you
for your protection?

555
00:52:18,180 --> 00:52:19,520
Pay me?

556
00:52:20,350 --> 00:52:21,950
[gentle scoff]

557
00:52:21,980 --> 00:52:24,190
Let me tell you something, Agent Peña.

558
00:52:24,980 --> 00:52:27,400
Maybe it'll make you feel better,
but maybe not.

559
00:52:28,530 --> 00:52:32,990
We're gonna get them someday.
But not your way.

560
00:52:34,030 --> 00:52:38,200
For everything you know, you're, uh...
extremely naive.

561
00:52:39,290 --> 00:52:40,950
Anyway, I've enjoyed this.

562
00:52:41,540 --> 00:52:42,770
The laughs.

563
00:52:42,790 --> 00:52:44,810
Um... Oh.

564
00:52:44,830 --> 00:52:46,880
I think the ambassador wants to see you.

565
00:52:47,630 --> 00:52:51,720
I guess word about this Miami Herald thing
is spreading like a prairie fire.

566
00:52:52,920 --> 00:52:54,130
And bring your passport.

567
00:52:55,050 --> 00:52:57,010
I think you're going home, but...

568
00:52:58,600 --> 00:53:00,390
you didn't hear that from me.

569
00:54:45,620 --> 00:54:46,970
Tata?

570
00:54:47,000 --> 00:54:48,330
[static]

571
00:54:52,000 --> 00:54:53,710
Tata, can you hear me?

572
00:54:54,500 --> 00:54:55,840
[Tata] Pablo?

573
00:54:58,590 --> 00:55:00,260
It's me, my love.

574
00:55:01,220 --> 00:55:03,350
Finally, I can speak to you, my love.

575
00:55:03,970 --> 00:55:05,600
I've missed you so much.

576
00:55:06,310 --> 00:55:08,310
Where have you been, Pablo?

577
00:55:11,650 --> 00:55:14,400
I had to do something very important.

578
00:55:18,400 --> 00:55:20,820
But I'm back home, my love.

579
00:55:23,950 --> 00:55:25,950
I'm home.

